<subSubSection id="6EDC654FFE45FF8EFF32FE115E2FFD4D" pageId="5" pageNumber="26" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="267936C4FE45FF8EFF32FE115E2FFD4D" blockId="5.[174,1233,415,890]" pageId="5" pageNumber="26">
Biology. 
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE45FF8EFEB6FE115E71FE4D" author="Rozkosny, R." box="[359,567,479,506]" pageId="5" pageNumber="26" pagination="117 - 160" refId="ref6777" refString="Rozkosny, R. 1967. Zur Morphologie und Biologie der Metamorphosestadien mitteleuropaischer Sciomyziden (Diptera). Acta Academiae Scientiarum, Brno, 1 (4), 117 - 160." type="journal article" year="1967">Rozkošný (1967)</bibRefCitation>
described the puparium and the cephalopharyngeal skeleton of the third instar larva extracted from this single puparium. The complete larval developmental and the life cycle have been explained by 
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE45FF8EFCEFFDD15F8FFD8D" author="Vala, J. - C." box="[830,969,543,570]" pageId="5" pageNumber="26" pagination="1 - 300" refId="ref7413" refString="Vala, J. - C. 1989. Dipteres Sciomyzidae Euro-mediterraneens. Faune de France. France et Regions limitrophes. N ° 72. Federation Francaise de la Societe des Sciences Naturelles, Paris. 1 - 300." type="book chapter" year="1989">Vala (1989)</bibRefCitation>
. In nature, third instar larva had been found to living as parasitoide in 
<taxonomicName id="E1C64D47FE45FF8EFD3EFD8E5FF7FDEE" box="[751,945,575,602]" class="Gastropoda" family="Succineidae" genus="Succinea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="5" pageNumber="26" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="elegans">
<emphasis id="14B2EAD6FE45FF8EFD3EFD8E5FF7FDEE" box="[751,945,575,602]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="26">Succinea elegans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and many eggs jointed by their extremities and laid along the veins of 
<taxonomicName id="E1C64D47FE45FF8EFD26FDAE5FF0FDCE" box="[759,950,607,633]" class="Liliopsida" family="Iridaceae" genus="Iris" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="5" pageNumber="26" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pseudacorus">
<emphasis id="14B2EAD6FE45FF8EFD26FDAE5FF0FDCE" box="[759,950,607,633]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="26">Iris pseudacorus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
leaves (
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE45FF8EFBC8FD9158D9FDCD" author="Vala, J. - C." box="[1049,1183,607,634]" pageId="5" pageNumber="26" pagination="1 - 300" refId="ref7413" refString="Vala, J. - C. 1989. Dipteres Sciomyzidae Euro-mediterraneens. Faune de France. France et Regions limitrophes. N ° 72. Federation Francaise de la Societe des Sciences Naturelles, Paris. 1 - 300." type="book chapter" year="1989">Vala, 1989</bibRefCitation>
). In laboratory, larvae attacked also 
<taxonomicName id="E1C64D47FE45FF8EFDF4FD4E5F84FD2D" authority="(Linnaeus, 1758)" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[549,962,639,666]" class="Gastropoda" family="Helicidae" genus="Cepaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="5" pageNumber="26" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="nemoralis">
<emphasis id="14B2EAD6FE45FF8EFDF4FD4E5EB3FD2E" box="[549,757,639,666]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="26">Cepaea nemoralis</emphasis>
(Linnaeus, 1758)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="E1C64D47FE45FF8EFC2EFD4E5E52FD0D" authority="(Linnaeus, 1758) (Vala, 1989)" authorityName="Vala" authorityYear="1989" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" class="Gastropoda" family="Hygromiidae" genus="Hygromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="5" pageNumber="26" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="hispida">
<emphasis id="14B2EAD6FE45FF8EFC2EFD4E5896FD2E" box="[1023,1232,639,665]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="26">Hygromia hispida</emphasis>
(Linnaeus, 1758) (
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE45FF8EFE56FD515E4AFD0D" author="Vala, J. - C." box="[391,524,671,698]" pageId="5" pageNumber="26" pagination="1 - 300" refId="ref7413" refString="Vala, J. - C. 1989. Dipteres Sciomyzidae Euro-mediterraneens. Faune de France. France et Regions limitrophes. N ° 72. Federation Francaise de la Societe des Sciences Naturelles, Paris. 1 - 300." type="book chapter" year="1989">Vala, 1989</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. The puparium is formed outside of snail host and can be parasitized by 
<emphasis id="14B2EAD6FE45FF8EFE83FD715D9BFD6E" box="[338,477,703,729]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="26">Mesoleptsus</emphasis>
spp.(Icheuneumonidae) (
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE45FF8EFCDDFD715FCAFD6D" author="Vala, J. - C." box="[780,908,703,730]" pageId="5" pageNumber="26" pagination="1 - 300" refId="ref7413" refString="Vala, J. - C. 1989. Dipteres Sciomyzidae Euro-mediterraneens. Faune de France. France et Regions limitrophes. N ° 72. Federation Francaise de la Societe des Sciences Naturelles, Paris. 1 - 300." type="book chapter" year="1989">Vala, 1989</bibRefCitation>
). This species is multivoltine and overwinters as pupa (
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE45FF8EFE0AFD115E1BFD4D" author="Vala, J. - C." box="[475,605,735,762]" pageId="5" pageNumber="26" pagination="1 - 300" refId="ref7413" refString="Vala, J. - C. 1989. Dipteres Sciomyzidae Euro-mediterraneens. Faune de France. France et Regions limitrophes. N ° 72. Federation Francaise de la Societe des Sciences Naturelles, Paris. 1 - 300." type="book chapter" year="1989">Vala, 1989</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="6EDC654FFE45FF8EFF32FCCE5F63FCCD" pageId="5" pageNumber="26" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="267936C4FE45FF8EFF32FCCE5F63FCCD" blockId="5.[174,1233,415,890]" pageId="5" pageNumber="26">
D i a g n o s t i c c h a r a c t e r s: whitish pruinose patches forming occipital spots fused in basal half (fig. 2, 
<emphasis id="14B2EAD6FE45FF8EFEAEFCEE5DCCFC8E" box="[383,394,800,825]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="26">c</emphasis>
), anterior orbital setae close to vertical setae than to anterior margin of frons (fig. 2, 
<emphasis id="14B2EAD6FE45FF8EFEB4FCF15D35FCEE" box="[357,371,831,857]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="26">b</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="14B2EAD6FE45FF8EFE53FC8E5DCBFCEE" box="[386,397,832,857]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="26">c</emphasis>
); antenna yellow, arista with long brown hairs (fig. 2, 
<emphasis id="14B2EAD6FE45FF8EFBC3FCF15866FCEE" box="[1042,1056,831,857]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="26">b</emphasis>
); wing hyaline slightly darkened as in fig. 1, 
<emphasis id="14B2EAD6FE45FF8EFDD3FCAE5E56FCCE" box="[514,528,864,889]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="26">a</emphasis>
; surstylus as in fig. 1, 
<emphasis id="14B2EAD6FE45FF8EFCDEFC915F58FCCE" box="[783,798,863,889]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="26">d</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
